latestPosts.caption:
When #NarcisoRodriguez founded his namesake brand in 1997, he quickly became a part of the go-go revolution in American sportswear that brought New York designers to the fashion forefront. He followed his muses throughout the stages of their lives, dressing the likes of #CarolynBessette, #JuliannaMargulies and#ClaireDanes. Now, after a COVID hiatus and a “personal reinvention,” Rodriguez is taking a quiet new approach to design.

“I just don’t want to be trapped in a machine,” he tells Fashion Features Director @veroniquehyland. “I want to get back to the things that bring me joy: my craft, the materials.” For ELLE’s April issue, the designer discusses redrawing the lines of his career. Head to the link in bio for more. 

Photo: Drew Jarrett
